#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn22.85"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn22.85:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 22 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 22 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:0.2"
msgid "9. Theravagga "
msgstr "9. Senior Mendicants "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.85:0.3"
msgid "85. Yamakasutta "
msgstr "85. With Yamaka "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "sn22.85:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ āyasmā sāriputto sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time Venerable Sāriputta was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena yamakassa nāma bhikkhuno evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "Now at that time a mendicant called Yamaka had the following harmful misconception: "

msgctxt "sn22.85:1.3"
msgid "“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“As I understand the Buddha’s teaching, a mendicant who has ended the defilements is annihilated and destroyed when their body breaks up, and doesn’t exist after death.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn22.85:2.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho sambahulā bhikkhū yamakassa kira nāma bhikkhuno evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "Several mendicants heard about this. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:2.2"
msgid "“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.85:2.3"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū yenāyasmā yamako tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā yamakena saddhiṃ sammodiṃsu. "
msgstr "They went to Yamaka and exchanged greetings with him. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:2.4"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ yamakaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When the greetings and polite conversation were over, they sat down to one side and said to him, "

#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.110, sc3
msgctxt "sn22.85:3.1"
msgid "“Saccaṃ kira te, āvuso yamaka, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ: "
msgstr "“Is it really true, Reverend Yamaka, that you have such a harmful misconception: "

msgctxt "sn22.85:3.2"
msgid "‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘As I understand the Buddha’s teaching, a mendicant who has ended the defilements is annihilated and destroyed when their body breaks up, and doesn’t exist after death.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:3.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ khvāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi: "
msgstr "“Yes, reverends, that’s how I understand the Buddha’s teaching.” "

msgctxt "sn22.85:3.4"
msgid "‘khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn22.85:4.1"
msgid "“Mā, āvuso yamaka, evaṃ avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi. Na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhācikkhanaṃ. Na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "“Don’t say that, Yamaka! Don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for misrepresentation of the Buddha is not good. And the Buddha would not say that.” "

msgctxt "sn22.85:4.2"
msgid "‘khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.85:4.3"
msgid "Evampi kho āyasmā yamako tehi bhikkhūhi vuccamāno tatheva taṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa voharati: "
msgstr "But even though admonished by those mendicants, Yamaka obstinately stuck to that misconception and insisted on stating it. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:4.4"
msgid "“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn22.85:5.1"
msgid "Yato kho te bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu āyasmantaṃ yamakaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetuṃ, atha kho te bhikkhū uṭṭhāyāsanā yenāyasmā sāriputto tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "When those mendicants were unable to dissuade Yamaka from that misconception, they got up from their seats and went to see Venerable Sāriputta. They told him what had happened, and said, "

msgctxt "sn22.85:5.2"
msgid "“yamakassa nāma, āvuso sāriputta, bhikkhuno evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.85:5.3"
msgid "‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.85:5.4"
msgid "Sādhāyasmā sāriputto yena yamako bhikkhu tenupasaṅkamatu anukampaṃ upādāyā”ti. "
msgstr "“May Venerable Sāriputta please go to the mendicant Yamaka out of compassion.” "

msgctxt "sn22.85:5.5"
msgid "Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā sāriputto tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "Sāriputta consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:5.6"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yenāyasmā yamako tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmatā yamakena saddhiṃ sammodi … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā sāriputto āyasmantaṃ yamakaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then in the late afternoon, Venerable Sāriputta came out of retreat, went to Venerable Yamaka and exchanged greetings with him. Seated to one side he said to Yamaka: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.111, sc6
msgctxt "sn22.85:6.1"
msgid "“Saccaṃ kira te, āvuso yamaka, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ: "
msgstr "“Is it really true, Reverend Yamaka, that you have such a harmful misconception: "

msgctxt "sn22.85:6.2"
msgid "‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘As I understand the Buddha’s teaching, a mendicant who has ended the defilements is annihilated and destroyed when their body breaks up, and doesn’t exist after death.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:6.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ khvāhaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes, reverend, that’s how I understand the Buddha’s teaching.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn22.85:7.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso yamaka, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Yamaka? "

msgctxt "sn22.85:7.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:7.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:7.4"
msgid "“Vedanā niccā … "
msgstr "“Is feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:7.5"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:7.6"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:7.7"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:7.8"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“Impermanent, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:7.9"
msgid "“Tasmātiha … pe … "
msgstr "“So you should truly see … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:7.10"
msgid "evaṃ passaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "Seeing this … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:7.11"
msgid "nāparaṃ itthattāyāti pajānāti. "
msgstr "They understand: ‘… there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "sn22.85:8.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso yamaka, "
msgstr "What do you think, Reverend Yamaka? "

msgctxt "sn22.85:8.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "Do you regard the Realized One as form?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:8.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso” … "
msgstr "“No, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:8.4"
msgid "“vedanaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "“Do you regard the Realized One as feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:8.5"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso” … "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.85:8.6"
msgid "“saññaṃ … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:8.7"
msgid "saṅkhāre … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:8.8"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "consciousness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:8.9"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“No, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn22.85:9.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso yamaka, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Reverend Yamaka? "

msgctxt "sn22.85:9.2"
msgid "rūpasmiṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "Do you regard the Realized One as in form?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:9.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“No, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:9.4"
msgid "“Aññatra rūpā tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "“Or do you regard the Realized One as distinct from form?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:9.5"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“No, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:9.6"
msgid "“Vedanāya … "
msgstr "“Do you regard the Realized One as in feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:9.7"
msgid "aññatra vedanāya … pe … "
msgstr "or distinct from feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:9.8"
msgid "saññāya … "
msgstr "as in perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:9.9"
msgid "aññatra saññāya … "
msgstr "or distinct from perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:9.10"
msgid "saṅkhāresu … "
msgstr "as in choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:9.11"
msgid "aññatra saṅkhārehi … "
msgstr "or distinct from choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:9.12"
msgid "viññāṇasmiṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "as in consciousness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:9.13"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“No, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:9.14"
msgid "“Aññatra viññāṇā tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "“Or do you regard the Realized One as distinct from consciousness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:9.15"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“No, reverend.” "

# NOTE: This passage is unclear, see discussion at https://discourse.suttacentral.net/t/a-problematic-reading-in-the-yamaka-sutta/2944
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "sn22.85:10.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso yamaka, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Yamaka? "

msgctxt "sn22.85:10.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ … vedanaṃ … saññaṃ … saṅkhāre … viññāṇaṃ tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "Do you regard the Realized One as possessing form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:10.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“No, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.112, sc11
msgctxt "sn22.85:11.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso yamaka, "
msgstr "“What do you think, Yamaka? "

msgctxt "sn22.85:11.2"
msgid "ayaṃ so arūpī … avedano … asaññī … asaṅkhāro … aviññāṇo tathāgatoti samanupassasī”ti? "
msgstr "Do you regard the Realized One as one who is without form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:11.3"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, āvuso”. "
msgstr "“No, reverend.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: thetato → tathato (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: tathāgate anupalabbhiyamāne → tathāgato anupalabbhiyamāno (s1-3, pts1) | tathāgate anupalabbhamāne (?)
msgctxt "sn22.85:11.4"
msgid "“Ettha ca te, āvuso yamaka, diṭṭheva dhamme saccato thetato tathāgate anupalabbhiyamāne, kallaṃ nu te taṃ veyyākaraṇaṃ: "
msgstr "“In that case, Reverend Yamaka, since you don’t acknowledge the Realized One as a genuine fact in the present life, is it appropriate to declare: "

msgctxt "sn22.85:11.5"
msgid "‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā khīṇāsavo bhikkhu kāyassa bhedā ucchijjati vinassati, na hoti paraṃ maraṇā’”ti? "
msgstr "‘As I understand the Buddha’s teaching, a mendicant who has ended the defilements is annihilated and destroyed when their body breaks up, and doesn’t exist after death.’?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "sn22.85:12.1"
msgid "“Ahu kho me taṃ, āvuso sāriputta, pubbe aviddasuno pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ; "
msgstr "“Reverend Sāriputta, in my ignorance, I used to have that misconception. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:12.2"
msgid "idañca panāyasmato sāriputtassa dhammadesanaṃ sutvā tañceva pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ pahīnaṃ, dhammo ca me abhisamito”ti. "
msgstr "But now that I’ve heard the teaching from Venerable Sāriputta I’ve given up that misconception, and I’ve comprehended the teaching.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "sn22.85:13.1"
msgid "“Sace taṃ, āvuso yamaka, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "“Reverend Yamaka, suppose they were to ask you: "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.2"
msgid "‘yo so, āvuso yamaka, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā kiṃ hotī’ti? "
msgstr "‘When their body breaks up, after death, what happens to a perfected one, who has ended the defilements?’ "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.3"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭho tvaṃ, āvuso yamaka, kinti byākareyyāsī”ti? "
msgstr "How would you answer?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:13.4"
msgid "“Sace maṃ, āvuso, evaṃ puccheyyuṃ: "
msgstr "“Sir, if they were to ask this, "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.5"
msgid "‘yo so, āvuso yamaka, bhikkhu arahaṃ khīṇāsavo so kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā kiṃ hotī’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.6"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ byākareyyaṃ: "
msgstr "I’d answer like this: "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.7"
msgid "‘rūpaṃ kho, āvuso, aniccaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, form is impermanent. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.8"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ; "
msgstr "What’s impermanent is suffering. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.9"
msgid "yaṃ dukkhaṃ taṃ niruddhaṃ tadatthaṅgataṃ. "
msgstr "What’s suffering has ceased and ended. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.85:13.10"
msgid "Vedanā … "
msgstr "Feeling … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.11"
msgid "saññā … "
msgstr "perception … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.12"
msgid "saṅkhārā … "
msgstr "choices … "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.13"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ aniccaṃ. "
msgstr "consciousness is impermanent. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.14"
msgid "Yadaniccaṃ taṃ dukkhaṃ; "
msgstr "What’s impermanent is suffering. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.15"
msgid "yaṃ dukkhaṃ taṃ niruddhaṃ tadatthaṅgatan’ti. "
msgstr "What’s suffering has ceased and ended.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.85:13.16"
msgid "Evaṃ puṭṭhohaṃ, āvuso, evaṃ byākareyyan”ti. "
msgstr "That’s how I’d answer such a question.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.113, sc14
msgctxt "sn22.85:14.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, āvuso yamaka. "
msgstr "“Good, good, Reverend Yamaka! "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.2"
msgid "Tena hāvuso yamaka, upamaṃ te karissāmi etasseva atthassa bhiyyoso mattāya ñāṇāya. "
msgstr "Well then, I shall give you a simile to make the meaning even clearer. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, āvuso yamaka, gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo; "
msgstr "Suppose there was a householder or householder’s son who was rich, with a lot of money and great wealth, "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.4"
msgid "so ca ārakkhasampanno. "
msgstr "and a bodyguard for protection. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.5"
msgid "Tassa kocideva puriso uppajjeyya anatthakāmo ahitakāmo ayogakkhemakāmo jīvitā voropetukāmo. "
msgstr "Then along comes a person who wants to harm, injure, and threaten him, and take his life. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.6"
msgid "Tassa evamassa: "
msgstr "They’d think: "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.7"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā aḍḍho mahaddhano mahābhogo; "
msgstr "‘This householder or householder’s son is rich, with a lot of money and great wealth, "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.8"
msgid "so ca ārakkhasampanno; "
msgstr "and a bodyguard for protection. "

#. VAR: nāyaṃ sukaro → na vyāsukaro (bj) | na hāyaṃ sukaro (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn22.85:14.9"
msgid "nāyaṃ sukaro pasayha jīvitā voropetuṃ. "
msgstr "It won’t be easy to take his life by force. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.10"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ anupakhajja jīvitā voropeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I get close to him, then take his life?’ "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.11"
msgid "So taṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatiputtaṃ vā upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadeyya: "
msgstr "So he goes up to that householder or householder’s son and says: "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.12"
msgid "‘upaṭṭhaheyyaṃ taṃ, bhante’ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, I would serve you.’ "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.13"
msgid "Tamenaṃ so gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā upaṭṭhāpeyya. "
msgstr "Then they would serve that householder or householder’s son. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.14"
msgid "So upaṭṭhaheyya pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṃkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī. "
msgstr "They’d get up before him and go to bed after him, and be obliging, behaving nicely and speaking politely. "

#. VAR: saddaheyya → daheyya (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn22.85:14.15"
msgid "Tassa so gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā mittatopi naṃ saddaheyya; "
msgstr "The householder or householder’s son would consider them as a friend "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.16"
msgid "suhajjatopi naṃ saddaheyya; "
msgstr "and companion, "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.17"
msgid "tasmiñca vissāsaṃ āpajjeyya. "
msgstr "and come to trust them. "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.18"
msgid "Yadā kho, āvuso, tassa purisassa evamassa: "
msgstr "But when that person realizes that "

msgctxt "sn22.85:14.19"
msgid "‘saṃvissattho kho myāyaṃ gahapati vā gahapatiputto vā’ti, atha naṃ rahogataṃ viditvā tiṇhena satthena jīvitā voropeyya. "
msgstr "they’ve gained the trust of the householder or householder’s son, then, when they know he’s alone, they’d take his life with a sharp knife. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.114, sc15
msgctxt "sn22.85:15.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, āvuso yamaka, "
msgstr "What do you think, Yamaka? "

msgctxt "sn22.85:15.2"
msgid "yadā hi so puriso amuṃ gahapatiṃ vā gahapatiputtaṃ vā upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ āha: "
msgstr "When that person went to the householder or householder’s son and offered to "

msgctxt "sn22.85:15.3"
msgid "‘upaṭṭhaheyyaṃ taṃ, bhante’ti, tadāpi so vadhakova. "
msgstr "serve him, weren’t they a killer then, "

msgctxt "sn22.85:15.4"
msgid "Vadhakañca pana santaṃ na aññāsi: "
msgstr "though he didn’t know that "

msgctxt "sn22.85:15.5"
msgid "‘vadhako me’ti. "
msgstr "this was his killer? "

msgctxt "sn22.85:15.6"
msgid "Yadāpi so upaṭṭhahati pubbuṭṭhāyī pacchānipātī kiṅkārapaṭissāvī manāpacārī piyavādī, tadāpi so vadhakova. "
msgstr "And when they got up before him and went to bed after him, being obliging, behaving nicely and speaking politely, weren’t they a killer then, "

msgctxt "sn22.85:15.7"
msgid "Vadhakañca pana santaṃ na aññāsi: "
msgstr "though he didn’t know that "

msgctxt "sn22.85:15.8"
